Q/A
Q: Why I can not connect with non-root users?
A: The docker commands are executed by the app without "sudo" so you will need to add your non-root user to the docker group with the following command:
sudo usermod -aG docker $USERsudo reboot

Q: Why I can not connect to Synology server with non-root user?
A: The non-root user has to in the docker group and also when ssh-ing to Synology server, the .bashrc profile is not loaded by default so the following command are required:
sudo synogroup --add docker $USER
sudo chown root:docker /var/run/docker.sock
sudo ln -s /volume1/@appstore/Docker/usr/bin/docker /usr/bin/docker
NOTE: "/volume1/@appstore/Docker/usr/bin/docker" might be different for your case.

Q: Why I can not connect to QNAP server with non-root user?
A: The non-root user has to in the docker group and also when ssh-ing to QNAP server, the .bashrc profile is not loaded by default so the following command are required:
sudo addgroup $USER administrators
sudo ln -s /share/CACHEDEV1_DATA/.qpkg/container-station/bin/docker /usr/bin/docker
NOTE: "/share/CACHEDEV1_DATA/.qpkg/container-station/bin/docker" might be different for your case.

Q: Why my ssh key is not working?
A: The ssh agent accepts only RSA format keys so if you are using another format (openssh) please convert it with the following command:
ssh-keygen -f -p -m pem -P PASSPHASE -N PASSPHASE
NOTE: add "" if there is no passphase for the ssh key

The collected data is used to improve the eye tracking algorithms that are developed and distributed by Eyeware in their research projects and products. An example of such a product is the Eyeware Beam iOS app, which turns your iPhone into a head and eye tracking device for gamers and streamers. In this case, gamers and streamers would directly benefit from the data collected by testers using the Eyeware Data Recorder iOS app: Beam users will have a smoother and increasingly pleasant experience using their iPhone or iPad as a head and eye tracker.

Eyeware Data Recorder is useful for scientific studies that will in the end increase the performance of eye tracking algorithms developed by Eyeware Tech.

The app records the user’s face area while following a sequence of points appearing on the screen of the device. The user is asked to watch a set of points that will be used as ground-truth. The data, in the form of videos and non-personal metadata, will be uploaded to Eyeware’s servers, and will then be used to help improve the performance of Eyeware’s gaze tracking algorithms.

All collected data is treated with the appropriate care in terms of confidentiality and security. The data is anonymized: users are asked for some personal details (name and email), but is stored on a separate server from the video data. Thus, no-one at Eyeware can have access to both the personal details and the video data. 

All collected data is not connected in any way to personal details of the data provider, i.e. the tester who is participating in the data collection activity. Collected data can be deleted at any moment by simply emailing us via the email address you provided for the sign up.
